My take
As KFC acknowledges, food supply chains are horribly complex and experience matters. KFC said that it had selected DHL for its track record of innovation but as this case illustrates, complexity and JIT can go wrong.
Assuming that DHL gets its act together, the adverse consequences for KFC may be short-livedÂ but, with 80% of the outlets under franchise ownership, there are questions to be asked around revenue and cost compensation.
